description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the wider Outpatient Pharmacy team by receiving and booking prescriptions to be dispensed and assisting with sales and other retail operations to ensure that the KFM Outpatient Pharmacy service runs smoothly and in line with our safety and quality standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The patients we serve have diverse healthcare needs, coming from across a range of outpatient clinics, and Accident &amp; Emergency at Denmark Hill. This means that no two days are the same and we work in a fast paced environment, your passion and enthusiasm will ensure that patients receive great service and the wider team are supported to prepare and supply medication as safely and efficiently as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work closely with your colleagues within the Outpatient Pharmacy, demonstrating our values and that ‘Working Together Gets It Done’, and ensuring that you deliver a high quality service, focussed on patient case.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be great with people and able to engage with patients from all walks of life with diverse healthcare needs. Although experience in a Pharmacy environment would be beneficial, your enthusiasm for working within healthcare &amp; pharmacy, alongside wanting to grow and develop will stand you in good stead for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KFM are committed to the development of all our staff and when you join KFM you will receive;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A nominated buddy / mentor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A development plan to support you during your initial probation period&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Annual appraisal and professional development planning&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support for ongoing professional study alongside your role with us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A range of internal training &amp; development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: &lt;strong&gt;20/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date:TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
